    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/9–1554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-15T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 15, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>233. Verbatim Text. Re Chinese representation; <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 146, September 14, and mytel 229 September 13. Moratorium
                    formula worked out with <gloss target="#t_UKDel1">UKDel</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> staff this afternoon confirmed over phone by
                    me with <persName corresp="#p_DIXONSPJ1">Dixon</persName> as following: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Decides not to consider, at its ninth session during the current year,
                            any proposals to exclude the representatives of the government of the
                            Republic of China or to seat representatives of the Central People’s
                            Government of the People’s Republic of China.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Procedures for handling Chinese representation at closing meeting eighth <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, 20 September, and opening ninth <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> to be worked out tomorrow with <gloss
                        target="#t_UKDel1">UKDel</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                    staff. Will attempt confirm this with <persName corresp="#p_DIXONSPJ1"
                        >Dixon</persName> Saturday a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
